$CMTH BAS

                      ^                           ^
                      ^   RECALCULATION METHODS   ^
                      ^                           ^

        The /OPTION RECALC command provides two methods for 
        recalculating the value of all worksheet cells:

 AUTOMATIC -- The entire worksheet is recalculated whenever you change
              the contents of a cell, or when you type the <CALC> key
              (as the first character) while Ready: is displayed.

 MANUAL    -- The entire worksheet is recalculated only when you press
              the <CALC> key (as the first character) while Ready: is
              displayed.  Select MANUAL when you want to postpone 
              recalculation until you are ready to compute any number 
              of changes all at once. /OPTION RECALC MANUAL is
              the initial default.


# BAS

                  ^ A FEW WORDS ABOUT IMMEDIATE CALCULATION ^

         You can enter a formula on the Edit Line, direct 20/20 to
         calculate the formula, and display its result -- all at once.
         This immediate calculation method affects only the specified
         cell; it does not recalculate the entire worksheet.

         To calculate a formula immediately, add an exclamation 
         point (!) to the end of the formula, then press <CR>.  To 
         enter the formula result into the current cell, press <CR> 
         once more.  That cell then contains the formula result; 
         not the formula.  
 

$CLO1 BAS

                          ^                     ^
                          ^ RECALCULATION ORDER ^
                          ^                     ^

         NATURAL Order is the order in which you would perform the
         recalculations if you were doing them by hand.  That is,
         a cell's value is recalculated only after all other cells
         referenced in the cell's formula have been recalculated.

         COLUMN ORDER  --   Recalculation begins at cell [0,0] and
                            proceeds across columns, one at a time.

         ROW ORDER     --   Recalculation begins at cell [0,0] and
                            proceeds down rows, one at a time.

#SRCO BAS

                   ^   SELECTING THE RECALCULATION ORDER   ^

         Recalculation ORDER is set with the /OPTION ORDER command. 
         The default ORDER of recalculation is NATURAL, which always
         results in all cells receiving their correct final values
         each time the worksheet is recalculated. 

         However, you cannot use NATURAL ORDER if there are recalculation 
         loops or circular references (cell [1,3] refers to cell [1,2] 
         and cell [1,2] refers to cell [1,3], etc.) in your model.
         Therefore, change the ORDER to COLUMN or ROW if there are
         recalculation loops or circular references in the model.



