$IRR FUNCS

                          ^                       ^
                          ^ IRR(expression,range) ^
                          ^                       ^

       Calculates the Internal Rate of Return of cash flow.

       The expression is the value of the investment and the range contains
       the periodic cash flows.

       The Internal Rate of Return is the interest rate necessary to yield
       a net present value of the investment of zero.  This interest rate
       is expressed in decimal form (.12 for 12%, etc.).

       IRR is the inverse function of PV.

       Example: 

           If [2,9] = 75, and [2,10] = 56, then IRR(45,[2,9..10]) = 1.23

