$STD FUNCS

                                  ^           ^
                                  ^ STD(list) ^
                                  ^           ^

         Calculates the unbiased STandard Deviation.  This is defined as
         the square root of the sum of the squares of the deviations of
         each value from the mean, divided by one less than the number of
         values.

         If the number of values is less than two, or if any of the
         values is text, then the result is ERR.

         Example:  

                 If [3,4] = 11, [3,5] = 15, and [3,6] = 20, then
                 STD([3,4..6]) = 4.5092

$SUM FUNCS

                                  ^           ^
                                  ^ SUM(list) ^
                                  ^           ^

         Calculates the SUM of all arguments in the list.  If an argument
         is a range, SUM calculates the sum of all cells in the range.  If
         any referenced cells are blank, they are treated as zeros.  If a
         referenced cell contains a label, the result is ERR.

         For example:

                                 SUM([7,3..20])
                                 SUM([7..10,4])
                                 SUM([3,5..7],[5,5..7],2*[8,0])

