$/C /

                                 ^ COPY ^

   Copies cells from one worksheet range to another.  Options are:

     EVERYTHING - Copies entire cell contents (formula, value, and format).

     FORMAT     - Copies only the format of the cell(s).  With /COPY 
                  FORMAT, you can easily preformat a cell range. 

     VALUE      - Copies only the value (number) and format (excluding 
                  formulas) of the cell(s).  With /COPY VALUE, you can 
                  store model results anywhere on the worksheet.

     Range prompts:     Source Range - The cell(s) you copy
                        Target Range - The cell(s) you copy to 

    Source and Target Ranges can be single cell, column, row, contiguous,
    or non-contiguous.  

