$/WH /W

                         ^ /WINDOW: HORIZONTAL or VERTICAL ^
   HORIZONTAL  
   or VERTICAL - Splits the screen once, horizontally or vertically, starting
                 at the column or row cell cursor position.  Each resulting
                 window can then be split once more in either direction,
                 allowing a maximum of four windows.
                 
                 You move from window to window by pressing a semicolon (;).

   Because each split occurs below or to the right of the cell cursor, you
   cannot split a window vertically with the cell cursor positioned at the
   rightmost worksheet column; nor can you split a window horizontally with 
   the cell cursor positioned at the bottom row of the worksheet. 

   DELETE, ERASE, and SYNCHRONIZE are displayed as options when the worksheet 
   is split into more than one window.

              Reference:  {/WS}1. DELETE, ERASE, and SYNCHRONIZE

$/WT /W

                             ^ /WINDOWS: Titles ^

   TITLES - Sets column and/or row titles along the top or left edge of a 
            worksheet window, causing the titles to remain displayed no
            matter where you scroll throughout the worksheet. You can set 
            titles in every worksheet window.  Options are:
 
         BOTH       - Sets column and row titles simultaneously.
         HORIZONTAL - Sets row titles.
         VERTICAL   - Sets column titles.
         NONE       - Clears all TITLES settings.

$/WR /W

                           ^ /WINDOW: REFRESH ^

     REFRESH  - Redisplays the worksheet window.  This is useful for 
                removing graphic displays, as well as characters generated 
                by sources other than 20/20 (such as operating system 
                prompts). 

$/WS /W

                    ^ /WINDOW:  DELETE ERASE SYNCHRONIZE ^

     DELETE       - Removes window splits, one at a time, in reverse order
                    of their creation.

     ERASE        - Removes all window splits at once.

     SYNCHRONIZE  - Synchronizes the scrolling of the upper left window
                    with the window containing the cell cursor.  If the
                    window split is vertical, the rows align and stay 
                    aligned as you scroll in either of the synchronized
                    windows.  If the split is horizontal, the columns
                    align.  Option:

      UNSYNCHRONIZE  - Unsynchronizes the upper left window with the window
                       containing the cell cursor.  Use this option before
                       you synchronize the upper left window with a new
                       window containing the cell cursor.
                       
